1
00:00:01,520 --> 00:00:02,560
Are you ready for the meeting?

2
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:04,520
Oh?

3
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,880
<i>She's been holed up in here.</i>

4
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,880
What's even in there?

5
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:18,360
I've never gone inside myself.
Who knows what's in there?

6
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:20,200
- Hey, Sarut.
- Hm?

7
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:22,840
If Anong is connected
to that police officer's death…

8
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:24,160
Mm.

9
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,440
Then this room
is definitely going to be searched.

10
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:29,560
You should take a look inside.

11
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,920
- Just in case there is something.
- Mm.

12
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,880
So we'll know how to handle it in time.

13
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:36,520
Anong,

14
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:39,800
why did I trust you this much?

15
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,800
Just leave her here.

16
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:45,000
What if she wakes up
and doesn't see her child?

17
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,080
Who's that?

18
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:48,680
I asked, who is it?

19
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:21,560
What the hell was that?

20
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:35,080
Uncle,

21
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:38,400
I just got to the office. You want me
to come back just to check on you?

22
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,720
That's impossible. My work will be ruined.

23
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,960
Wait. Listen to me.

24
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:45,400
I'm not asking you
to come keep me company.

25
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:48,400
I want you
to check your aunt's room with me.

26
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:50,360
You're an engineer.

27
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:52,520
You'd understand things
better than I would.

28
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,600
Oh?

29
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:57,240
Didn't you say you already hired engineers

30
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:59,320
when you tried to kick me out?

31
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:02,800
Then call your own technicians again.

32
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:06,000
Listen to me.
Stop talking back for a second.

33
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,880
I'm doing this for your own good.

34
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:09,720
Or do you want outsiders
coming in to inspect your aunt's room

35
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,720
and seeing what's inside?

36
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:14,040
Who knows what's hidden inside?

37
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,840
I'm telling you.

38
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:19,040
I warned you.

39
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:21,160
If you won't come, then fine.

40
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:23,760
What?

41
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,520
Is he crazy?

42
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,560
Hello, Uncle Rut.

43
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:33,240
Call me back if you need anything.

44
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:35,360
I couldn't hear clearly. The line got cut.

45
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:41,880
After we finish talking
in Mr. Arnon's room,

46
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:44,080
should we go see my grandpa?

47
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:46,800
Oh. I was thinking the same thing.

48
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:49,360
I wanted to go there too.

49
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:51,800
- Mm.
- I want to ask him about my signs.

50
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:53,960
Why?

51
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:58,440
Did you see something new again?

52
00:05:58,520 --> 00:05:59,680
No.

53
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:03,320
I just feel like
you've been stressed lately.

54
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:05,680
Or maybe we switched bodies.

55
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,200
Yeah.

56
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:10,040
Possible.

57
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:12,080
Hey, he's here.

58
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:13,880
You're at the office early today.

59
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:17,480
Is he talking to us?

60
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,680
Yeah, I think so.

61
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:25,120
Uh, Mr. Warat,
I've sent you the revised project.

62
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:26,840
Have you had a chance to review it?

63
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:30,040
What project? I have no idea
what you're talking about.

64
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,200
You didn't receive it?

65
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:34,440
Mr. Chatchai
must be messing with me again.

66
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:36,520
I'll follow up on it right away.

67
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:39,200
Did I miss something?

68
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:41,560
Is there a meeting?
Why is everyone here so early?

69
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:43,000
No.

70
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:45,120
Just a normal workday.

71
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,720
Really? I thought I missed something.

72
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:49,160
I've been in the hospital for days.

73
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,960
I'm happy for my Grandma

74
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:56,960
that her trusted person
is this hardworking.

75
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:59,400
Not really, Mr. Warat.

76
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:03,600
I just want to fix what I did wrong.

77
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,960
Being sick made me realize…

78
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,800
I need to

79
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,560
do better.

80
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:16,520
So I want to make the most of my time now.

81
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:20,440
Kluay, if there's anything
I can help with, just tell me.

82
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:23,480
I'll go get that file now. Excuse me.

83
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,200
See that?

84
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,400
Tone it down.

85
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,600
I'm jealous.

86
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:39,440
Oh please, don't be ridiculous.

87
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:42,160
I'm not thinking anything.
I'm just surprised

88
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:44,880
that he suddenly started being so nice.

89
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,160
You can tell he's fake.

90
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:50,440
Hey, that's not nice.

91
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:51,920
It's the truth.

92
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,360
- Come on.
- Look at his face.

93
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,200
Look into his eyes and you'll see.

94
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:57,480
- See what?
- His real intentions.

95
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,280
Kluay.

96
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:03,040
- Oh?
- Mr. Warat, hello.

97
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:05,520
- Hello.
- I was just about to come see you.

98
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:08,000
I didn't imagine things, did I?

99
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:11,280
Was Jirasin actually
talking to you two and even bowing?

100
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:13,240
You saw it right.

101
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:14,680
And he was extra fake too.

102
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,400
Hey, Mr. Warat.

103
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,960
- What?
- Why are you talking about him like that?

104
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,600
Why can't I?

105
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:22,240
- Huh?
- Or do you like him?

106
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:25,320
No, this is the workplace.
You can't talk about people like that.

107
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,840
Good morning, everyone.

108
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,200
Mm.

109
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:29,960
Looks like there are
lots of surprises today.

110
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:34,360
Hey, earlier I saw Jirasin acting all cute

111
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:37,120
- and clingy with you two.
- Clingy?

112
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,240
Uh…

113
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:42,799
Did you two make up?

114
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:44,120
Wait.

115
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,720
- Of course.
- Wait a second.

116
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:46,960
Wait.

117
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,960
Hey, what are you two gossiping about?

118
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:52,240
Hey.

119
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,240
- What is this?
- Oh.

120
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:58,800
- Oh, it's nothing, Som.
- Hey.

121
00:08:58,880 --> 00:09:01,080
- It's good news, right?
- No.

122
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:02,840
Hey.

123
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,520
Arnon, look.

124
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:08,440
- Kluay and Mr. Warat? Kluay, wait for me.
- Come here, come here.

125
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:15,400
Wow, my boss is amazing. That ring move?

126
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,840
So sharp.

127
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:20,160
You should do it too. Make it happen.

128
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:23,720
If you wait any longer,
you'll miss your chance.

129
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:26,040
Me?

130
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:29,680
Yeah, wait too long
and someone else will take her.

131
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:32,280
- I should really do it now?
- You should.

132
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:38,400
Propose? Give Som a ring?

133
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:41,040
What?

134
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:44,840
Mr. Chatchai, what's wrong with you?

135
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,760
Why did you do this?

136
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:49,400
You put the file on my desk
without telling me.

137
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:51,080
How was I supposed to know?

138
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:53,200
We need a new agreement.

139
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:56,680
If you don't come to me, I'll come to you.
How many times do I have to say

140
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:58,520
we need to give in for now?

141
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:00,720
Sin.

142
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:05,160
HEAD OF ENGINEERING ROOM

143
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:08,080
Why is it so hard to find?

144
00:10:08,160 --> 00:10:10,720
Right? Men in this country…

145
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,160
Arnon.

146
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:13,840
Are you busy with work?

147
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:16,800
I have some gossip.

148
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:18,080
Did you know

149
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:20,560
the ring Mr. Warat used
to propose to Kluay

150
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:21,920
belonged to Ms. Praewilai,

151
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,720
his mother?

152
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:25,760
I'm so jealous.

153
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:28,760
Of course, he's handsome and rich.

154
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:32,560
Why do you look strange?

155
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:36,440
And what are you looking at?
Why are you covering it with that file?

156
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:39,960
What are you looking at?

157
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:42,120
The light is too bright.

158
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,560
It hurts my eyes,
so I covered it with something.

159
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:46,240
The dimmer switch is broken.

160
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:50,240
I don't believe you. Let me see.

161
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:52,680
Arnon, move your hand.

162
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:56,720
So this is what you were looking at?

163
00:10:58,920 --> 00:10:59,960
Are you ready for the meeting?

164
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:01,920
Oh?

165
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:08,000
JEWELRY

166
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:14,600
Did you order
the ring I asked you to order yet?

167
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:19,400
Mr. Warat.

168
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:22,120
You had Arnon find these things for you?

169
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,440
Of course. The client is waiting.

170
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:25,640
Let me see.

171
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:27,120
Is it ready?

172
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:29,120
There are many styles, bracelets,

173
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:31,880
rings, and…

174
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,200
- necklaces as well.
- I…

175
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:35,680
I told you to find items

176
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:37,400
- with big discounts.
- Oh.

177
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:39,120
- Let me see.
- Here.

178
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:43,640
This one looks nice.

179
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:57,280
You gave it to me.

180
00:11:58,320 --> 00:11:59,920
I can do whatever I want with it.

181
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:02,720
I just wanted to say

182
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:05,720
that dwarf jasmine
was Lak's favorite flower.

183
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,320
So I got one for you.

184
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:10,480
Please place it

185
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:13,160
in front of Lak's photo for me.

186
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,840
Honestly,

187
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:17,760
you could use your stupidity as a shield.

188
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:18,680
That's effective.

189
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:19,880
What?

190
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:24,640
Sometimes you're so stupid

191
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:27,280
I don't even want to lower myself
to argue with you.

192
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,800
Sin,

193
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:34,000
weren't you going to be nice to me?

194
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,680
Never.

195
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:37,800
And not just you,

196
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:41,040
that so-called prince of yours too.

197
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:44,840
Why are you doing this?

198
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:47,400
You'll find out soon enough.

199
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:52,280
And don't even think about
running off to tell Warat or his grandma.

200
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:55,080
No one will believe you.

201
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:58,000
Everyone knows we're enemies.

202
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:01,680
No matter how much
you twist the story about me,

203
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:05,760
I can just pretend to be nice,

204
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:07,920
and everyone will believe me.

205
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:12,320
Yeah, you really are fake.

206
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:14,480
What did you say?

207
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:22,960
AMPHA

208
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,360
This is exactly

209
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:26,440
what they say, that criminals

210
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:28,440
always leave traces behind.

211
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:30,240
It just depends on
whether anyone finds them.

212
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:31,280
So, did you find anything?

213
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,600
No.

214
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:36,520
It's hard to believe that
such a small woman could cause all this

215
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,440
without getting caught.

216
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,880
I think it's just that
no one has found it yet.

217
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:42,680
But at least it's good

218
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:45,720
that Jirasin has calmed down like this.

219
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,880
It makes things easier for us.

220
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:49,640
How do you know he's calm?

221
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:52,520
I will never play along with his game.

222
00:13:58,720 --> 00:13:59,640
How is it?

223
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:03,160
Did you get any plants? The girls said
they went plant shopping.

224
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:04,680
Yes.

225
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,920
I already dedicated it
to the wandering spirits.

226
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:07,840
Oh?

227
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,680
Mr. Warat,

228
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:15,040
would it be possible for me
to review all the files

229
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:16,440
related to Sin's work?

230
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:17,640
Sure.

231
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:20,000
I was just about to discuss that with you.

232
00:14:20,640 --> 00:14:23,440
There's also my landscape budget involved.

233
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:25,200
Not just this project.

234
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,880
I want to review everything.

235
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:29,520
Okay.

236
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:37,160
Mr. Warat, can you teach me
how to get angry faster?

237
00:14:41,560 --> 00:14:44,440
So, are we going to have
a meeting about Anong today?

238
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:52,400
Let's deal with both aunt and nephew.

239
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:02,800
Alright, let's do it.

240
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:27,520
Sin…

241
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:31,240
How could you leave me here like this?

242
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:55,480
Go away.

243
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:05,480
Are we being attacked?

244
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:12,000
The lock isn't even that big.
Why is it so hard to break?

245
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:13,400
That's how old locks are.

246
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:15,960
Then just break it.
It's fine. I'll fix it later.

247
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:17,160
Go ahead, break it.

248
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,160
Hey!

249
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,800
What's all the shouting about?
What happened?

250
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,600
‪-Hey!
‪-Snakes!

251
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:24,880
- Hey!
- A snake nest!

252
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,160
- It's coming this way!
- Hurry, get it out first!

253
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,920
- Hurry, it's coming!
- Hurry, hurry!

254
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:30,360
- Hey!
- Call the fire department!

255
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,640
Okay. I'm coming.

256
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:40,920
I'm on my way now.

257
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:52,880
It's the same chemical.

258
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:55,280
So that means it's the same person.

259
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:57,920
Is it possible
that it could be different people?

260
00:16:58,520 --> 00:16:59,520
Anything's possible.

261
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:02,000
But in this case, I think

262
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:07,240
it's highly likely to be the same person.

263
00:17:07,319 --> 00:17:13,319
More importantly, this chemical
is not something you can easily find.

264
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:18,480
The key point is both Ms. Kluay and I
were exposed to it at the same time.

265
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,720
So this is attempted murder, right?

266
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:22,800
Does Jirasin know?

267
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:24,520
I'm not sure.

268
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,920
But if Anong did this,

269
00:17:29,560 --> 00:17:31,160
there must be a reason.

270
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:33,800
Whether it's related or not,
we'll find out.

271
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:35,040
If she really did it,

272
00:17:36,440 --> 00:17:39,280
she must have left some trace.
I'll go check.

273
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:42,600
Alright, I'll leave it to you.
I have to go.

274
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:43,960
Kluay, come on.

275
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:47,520
- I'm coming too.
- Hey, wait for me, Mr. Warat.

276
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:51,840
Come in.

277
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:56,120
Excuse me, Mom.

278
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,720
Here are the revised documents.

279
00:17:58,520 --> 00:18:01,280
Thank you for yielding to Warat.

280
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:03,880
It's not like that.

281
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:08,640
Everything Mr. Warat
pointed out was correct.

282
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:10,960
It was my mistake
for not checking carefully.

283
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:15,120
If you two can reconcile like this,

284
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:18,040
then I can finally step down.

285
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,480
Mr. Warat and I both
care about Vanich equally.

286
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:23,600
I believe we can work together.

287
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:25,720
Thank you.

288
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:28,520
Have a seat.

289
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:32,880
You know

290
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:35,440
I never let anyone work for free.

291
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:40,600
If you mean me, you don't need to worry.

292
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:43,400
I don't want anything.

293
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:45,760
Just the kindness
you've shown me all this time,

294
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:47,560
I can never repay it fully.

295
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:52,960
On the will opening day,
you have to come. You know that, right?

296
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:58,040
If that's what you want, then of course.

297
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:00,720
I have something important
prepared for you.

298
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:06,720
AUNT NONG

299
00:19:07,360 --> 00:19:08,400
Answer it.

300
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,240
It's okay, Mom.

301
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:12,520
Go ahead.

302
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:14,840
It must be important.

303
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:16,680
Otherwise, they wouldn't keep calling.

304
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,200
Then, please excuse me.

305
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:26,800
Aunt Nong.

306
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:30,200
Hello?

307
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:41,040
Why are you even thinking about Jirasin?

308
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:43,240
How did you know I was thinking about Sin?

309
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:44,720
You just said it.

310
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:47,040
Someone like him,
you don't need many words

311
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:51,720
to know what he's like.

312
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:55,800
I just don't understand
why he has to act like this.

313
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:58,160
If he doesn't actually
want to reconcile with us,

314
00:19:58,680 --> 00:20:01,080
then why pretend to give in to everything?

315
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:03,200
Because he has no choice.

316
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,000
Mr. Arnon and I

317
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:08,080
have prepared tons of evidence
to interrogate him with.

318
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:11,640
He must know that if he fights back,
he'll be completely ruined.

319
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:14,320
That's why he surrendered,

320
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:16,560
pretending to raise the white flag.

321
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:17,920
But who knows?

322
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:20,400
You guys really deal with stuff like this?

323
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:21,600
Don't you ever get tired?

324
00:20:21,680 --> 00:20:23,720
I just got involved recently,

325
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:25,920
and it's already this bad.

326
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:29,320
Before this, he and Mr. Chatchai

327
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,880
must have been involved
in a lot of corruption.

328
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:36,680
I really am as stupid as Sin said.

329
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:38,840
How could I even believe in him?

330
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:40,480
Kluay,

331
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:44,840
don't say that. You're not stupid.

332
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:48,200
Jirasin is just a bad person.

333
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:59,560
Let's stop talking about stressful things.

334
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:03,960
Let's talk about us instead.

335
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:06,560
What are you talking about?

336
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:09,000
Being together feels so good.

337
00:21:09,520 --> 00:21:11,200
If I had known,
I would've asked you out sooner.

338
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:15,400
No way.

339
00:21:15,480 --> 00:21:17,560
You're not off the hook yet.

340
00:21:17,640 --> 00:21:19,000
What are you talking about?

341
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:20,720
Of course I'm off the hook.

342
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:23,360
Otherwise, would we be engaged?

343
00:21:24,640 --> 00:21:28,480
- You always jump to conclusions.
- Let me see the ring.

344
00:21:28,560 --> 00:21:29,800
Let me see.

345
00:21:31,320 --> 00:21:33,600
Oh wow, the ring is so cute.

346
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:35,400
Mr. Warat.

347
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:37,280
What if someone sees us?

348
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:39,800
If anyone looks, I'll fire them.

349
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:42,680
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

350
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:44,280
Babe,

351
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:46,600
you want to go on a date today?

352
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:48,880
I booked a fine dining restaurant.

353
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:51,320
Maybe not yet.

354
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:54,960
I'm not sure if I can get
past your grandma first.

355
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:58,920
I want to make her feel at ease
that I won't put you in danger.

356
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:02,080
Don't forget,

357
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:05,200
she saw me coughing up blood,
almost dying.

358
00:22:05,280 --> 00:22:07,240
I understand how she feels.

359
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,040
Please.

360
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:10,960
Okay.

361
00:22:12,120 --> 00:22:13,840
Then, another day.

362
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:18,360
Let's wait until we sort out
your mother's case

363
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:20,600
and help Ms. Ampha first.

364
00:22:20,680 --> 00:22:22,920
- Alright?
- Okay.

365
00:22:27,960 --> 00:22:29,040
Let me kiss your cheek.

366
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:31,840
Mr. Warat, this is the office.

367
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:35,320
- If anyone looks, I'll fire them.
- No, hey.

368
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:36,560
No.

369
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,760
This is the office.

370
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:42,080
There are security cameras.

371
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:44,000
It's fine. We're engaged now.

372
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:45,720
But it's still the office.

373
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:50,880
Oh right, I have something else.

374
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:54,560
I feel like on the day
of the will reading,

375
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:57,320
something important might happen.

376
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:59,120
Can I go with you?

377
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:00,440
You can.

378
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:03,360
Don't forget we're engaged.

379
00:23:05,240 --> 00:23:06,360
Thank you.

380
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:11,320
Once everything is over,

381
00:23:12,040 --> 00:23:14,280
we'll finally be able
to be happy together.

382
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:16,440
Okay?

383
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:30,040
- I brought documents for Ms. Kluay.
- Sure.

384
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:33,040
- But I need to hand them over myself.
- No, you can't.

385
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:40,480
You can't. Sorry.

386
00:23:49,320 --> 00:23:50,400
What's going on?

387
00:23:50,480 --> 00:23:51,960
He's here to see Ms. Kluay.

388
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:53,720
What happened?

389
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:55,680
I saw you talking
for quite a while earlier.

390
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:57,520
He came to see you, Ms. Kluay.

391
00:23:57,600 --> 00:23:59,160
To see me?

392
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:01,120
Then why didn't you call me?

393
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:03,440
He didn't seem trustworthy.

394
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:06,480
When I asked, he only said
it was important documents

395
00:24:06,560 --> 00:24:08,840
and must be delivered to you personally.

396
00:24:08,920 --> 00:24:11,320
But he wouldn't give any details.

397
00:24:19,480 --> 00:24:20,720
PURCHASE COMES WITH
A BEAUTIFULLY PACKAGED BOX

398
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:27,320
This one is pretty.
It suits you. Just buy it.

399
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,880
Are you crazy?
It's just the beginning of the month.

400
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:31,760
Exactly. We just got paid.

401
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:33,640
I've used it up.

402
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:34,640
Seriously?

403
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:36,520
- Yeah.
- What did you spend it on?

404
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:44,840
Hey, this necklace
would match our mall uniform perfectly.

405
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:46,400
- I want it.
- Let me see.

406
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:47,680
Here, buy it.

407
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:51,040
Do I really look that old to you?

408
00:24:55,680 --> 00:24:58,200
Hey, let me ask you something.

409
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:02,440
If your boyfriend looked at reviews

410
00:25:02,520 --> 00:25:06,320
or websites about jewelry
necklaces, rings, stuff like that,

411
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:07,600
what would you think?

412
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:09,480
My boyfriend?

413
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:13,760
He's definitely cheating.

414
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:17,760
Cheating?

415
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:19,440
Then why are you asking?

416
00:25:19,520 --> 00:25:20,400
- Hey?
- Hey.

417
00:25:20,480 --> 00:25:22,600
- Don't tell me you're hiding a boyfriend?
- No, stop.

418
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:24,520
- Not even a boyfriend yet.
- Oh?

419
00:25:25,120 --> 00:25:26,960
I don't have anyone.

420
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:28,520
- Nothing at all.
- Whoa.

421
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:30,320
Alright, back to work.

422
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:39,760
What are you girls gossiping about?

423
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:42,600
- Just talking about boyfriends.
- Oh.

424
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:43,800
- Nothing, Arnon.
- Hm?

425
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:45,480
Where are you going? I'll go with you.

426
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:47,200
- Huh?
- Let's go.

427
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:48,120
Hm?

428
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:52,520
Are you keeping a secret from me?

429
00:25:53,040 --> 00:25:54,520
Are you talking about yourself?

430
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:56,120
Oh.

431
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:57,400
It circled back to me?

432
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:00,200
Something's going on, right?

433
00:26:00,720 --> 00:26:03,240
No. What could possibly be going on?

434
00:26:03,320 --> 00:26:05,520
We're nothing to each other.

435
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:11,360
Do you know Mama Toi
has a meeting with the chairwoman?

436
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:12,800
I know.

437
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:15,800
The Baan Saeng team
is rushing documents like crazy.

438
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:18,320
I can't believe it.

439
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:20,440
She looks so nice and calm.

440
00:26:21,840 --> 00:26:23,880
I think it's because of the DNA results

441
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:26,160
from the unidentified bodies
that haven't progressed.

442
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:28,680
So she has to handle it herself.

443
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:31,320
That's normal.

444
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,440
Ms. Kluay was poisoned.

445
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:36,200
Any mother would be worried.

446
00:26:36,280 --> 00:26:37,760
Not just Kluay,

447
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:40,640
you were poisoned by Anong too.

448
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:43,800
Keep your voice down.
Her nephew might hear.

449
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:45,600
- Jirasin?
- Shh.

450
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:46,520
Be quiet.

451
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:48,520
Let him hear it.

452
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:51,000
Maybe he'll realize
how rotten their whole group is.

453
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:54,080
He should stop acting like a hero.
And Kluay too.

454
00:26:54,160 --> 00:26:57,360
She even bought plants
to try to make peace with him.

455
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:59,400
- Just wait, it'll backfire.
- Hm.

456
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:01,160
No need to wait. It already did.

457
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:04,040
In the meeting, she looked like
she wanted to kill someone.

458
00:27:05,760 --> 00:27:06,640
But that's good.

459
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:09,000
A strong female lead
makes things more interesting.

460
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:11,760
And in the end,
the younger sister always comes to help.

461
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:13,720
If anyone messes with her,

462
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:14,840
I'll deal with them.

463
00:27:16,040 --> 00:27:19,400
Alright, I gotta go.
I have an appointment.

464
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:21,680
Wait, Som. Today we…

465
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:25,680
What's wrong with her?

466
00:27:32,040 --> 00:27:35,240
The will you asked me to handle
is all taken care of.

467
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:40,120
MR. WARAT VANICH

468
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:42,520
Good. Proceed as planned.

469
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:45,000
Please forgive me, ma'am,

470
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:49,600
I think you don't need
to rush this decision just yet.

471
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:50,760
What do you mean by that?

472
00:27:50,840 --> 00:27:53,800
You should wait until the truth
about Ms. Waree is clear first.

473
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:56,720
No matter what, Ms. Waree is still
your real granddaughter.

474
00:27:57,320 --> 00:27:59,160
And Warat is my real grandson too.

475
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:01,520
With the utmost respect,

476
00:28:01,600 --> 00:28:03,280
but this matter…

477
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:07,800
Poor Mr. Wichan, don't you think?

478
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:09,320
Mm, yeah.

479
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:11,840
Ms. Ampha must really
have reached her limit.

480
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:13,600
That's why she decided
to run away like that.

481
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:15,600
Just look at it,

482
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:17,640
raising someone else's child,

483
00:28:17,720 --> 00:28:18,840
in the end,

484
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:20,920
the person you truly love the most
is the one you hurt.

485
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:27,840
<i>I'm torn too, honestly,</i>

486
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:30,880
about whether Waree
is really still alive or not.

487
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:32,760
And how much can we really trust

488
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:35,360
what Kluay says?

489
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:38,600
Most importantly, if Waree is still alive,

490
00:28:38,680 --> 00:28:40,800
it's been 20 years already.

491
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:43,200
So why hasn't my granddaughter
come back to find me?

492
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:49,120
I think Ms. Waree may not even know
that she is an heiress to Vanich.

493
00:28:50,960 --> 00:28:54,120
Or maybe Kluay just imagined it.

494
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:58,560
- Maybe my granddaughter actually…
- Pong, Soi, Ms. Waree, and Ms. Ampha,

495
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:00,600
all four of them.
From what we've investigated,

496
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:03,000
they have no death registrations
on record.

497
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:06,760
Then let's publicly announce
that we're looking for Waree.

498
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:09,160
That would be
absolutely impossible, ma'am.

499
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:12,840
If we do that, there'll be all sorts
of impostors showing up.

500
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:16,800
So that means
we have to keep investigating quietly?

501
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:18,040
Yes, ma'am.

502
00:29:22,560 --> 00:29:23,680
- Supol.
- Yes, ma'am.

503
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:24,840
Get the car ready.

504
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:26,320
Where are you going?

505
00:29:26,880 --> 00:29:28,880
There's somewhere
I want to go see for myself.

506
00:29:48,760 --> 00:29:51,320
What's troubling you?

507
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:54,280
Uh…

508
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:55,680
Well…

509
00:29:58,040 --> 00:29:59,200
Work, right?

510
00:29:59,280 --> 00:30:00,680
Draw three cards, okay?

511
00:30:00,760 --> 00:30:02,440
Draw them and place them right here.

512
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:04,400
Let's see.

513
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:08,640
Your work looks good.

514
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:11,440
Very soon, you may even be promoted.

515
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:15,120
- I see.
- Now let's look at your health.

516
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:16,920
Three more cards, please.

517
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:20,800
Your health is fine.

518
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:22,600
Nothing to worry about.

519
00:30:23,640 --> 00:30:26,480
Here, the Strength card.

520
00:30:26,560 --> 00:30:28,000
It means

521
00:30:28,080 --> 00:30:30,800
you're very healthy. At most,

522
00:30:30,880 --> 00:30:33,360
it'll only be minor illness.

523
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:37,440
Actually,

524
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:41,760
I also sell OPD insurance.

525
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:44,360
No need to pay upfront either. Interested?

526
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:47,720
Wow, full service?

527
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:49,120
Just a little.

528
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:50,440
Well,

529
00:30:50,520 --> 00:30:53,400
what about love?

530
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:54,920
Three more cards, please.

531
00:30:59,880 --> 00:31:01,120
Love…

532
00:31:06,040 --> 00:31:08,080
If you don't have a boyfriend yet,

533
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:10,880
you'll be single for quite a while.

534
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:14,680
But if you already have a partner,

535
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:18,160
your boyfriend may cheat on you.

536
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:21,640
Cheat on me?

537
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:25,440
And how long have you been seeing him?

538
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:26,840
Draw one more.

539
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:30,480
Here you go.

540
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:35,520
Are you really sure
you're already with him?

541
00:31:35,600 --> 00:31:38,800
The cards say you're only just talking.

542
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:46,200
Well, we're just seeing each other.

543
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:50,360
He hasn't properly asked me
to be his girlfriend yet.

544
00:31:50,440 --> 00:31:51,440
Mm.

545
00:31:56,880 --> 00:32:00,280
Take this pendant
and have your boyfriend carry it.

546
00:32:00,360 --> 00:32:04,960
This pendant will help
drive away all evil things

547
00:32:05,040 --> 00:32:07,720
from your boyfriend.

548
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:11,480
No way.

549
00:32:11,560 --> 00:32:13,080
That's ridiculous. Who would believe that?

550
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:18,880
Arnon.

551
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:21,360
Now I have to do all kinds of things.

552
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:28,200
Hello?

553
00:32:29,400 --> 00:32:31,160
Oh, you can start the meeting.

554
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:32,800
I'll come in and listen in a bit.

555
00:32:33,320 --> 00:32:34,200
Yes.

556
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:53,920
- So? Did you find anything?
- Oh.

557
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:55,760
It's hard to find, Mr. Warat.

558
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:57,600
Is it really that hard?

559
00:32:57,680 --> 00:32:59,040
Of course it is, Mr. Warat.

560
00:32:59,120 --> 00:33:01,440
We don't know what the woman we like

561
00:33:01,520 --> 00:33:03,480
likes or dislikes.

562
00:33:03,560 --> 00:33:04,680
But I think

563
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:08,200
if you know what she likes,
just buy it. Go for it.

564
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:13,200
You've figured it out now, right?

565
00:33:13,280 --> 00:33:15,400
I think if you really
think about it, you'll get it.

566
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:17,000
Just go back and think carefully.

567
00:33:17,080 --> 00:33:21,520
What does the woman you like wear
that makes her look beautiful and amazing?

568
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:24,440
- Well…
- I think

569
00:33:24,520 --> 00:33:25,760
you should
look carefully at what kind of ring

570
00:33:25,840 --> 00:33:27,840
Som wears that makes her look…

571
00:33:27,920 --> 00:33:29,760
wow! You don't need
to consult me that much.

572
00:33:29,840 --> 00:33:31,840
I was trying to tell you that's my coffee.

573
00:33:38,840 --> 00:33:41,240
I'm really out of it.
I've got too much work.

574
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,520
You should help me sometimes.

575
00:33:45,480 --> 00:33:46,800
What documents?

576
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:49,840
All documents related to Mr. Jirasin.

577
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:51,880
Uh…

578
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,400
What do you need them for?

579
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:57,640
I just have something I need to verify.

580
00:33:59,760 --> 00:34:01,240
I'm sorry,

581
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:04,880
but these documents
are confidential company records.

582
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:08,000
We can't give them to

583
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:09,840
an outsider.

584
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:11,840
If you really want them,

585
00:34:11,920 --> 00:34:14,199
you'll have to submit a formal request
through the proper procedure.

586
00:34:14,880 --> 00:34:16,440
I'm really sorry.

587
00:34:23,719 --> 00:34:25,639
Can you hand over the documents now?

588
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:37,159
Here.

589
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:53,880
Mr. Chatchai?

590
00:35:00,240 --> 00:35:02,680
Don't think no one knows what you've done.

591
00:35:07,800 --> 00:35:10,040
Mr. Warat,
there's a visitor here to see you.

592
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:21,080
Why are you here?

593
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:26,760
We still have a lot of business
to coordinate together, Warat.

594
00:35:29,720 --> 00:35:30,960
Ameena.

595
00:35:31,040 --> 00:35:33,480
I have too much work. I'm exhausted.

596
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:34,840
Please go back.

597
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:38,440
Dad just informed me

598
00:35:38,520 --> 00:35:41,720
that he plans to make
a major investment with Vanich Mall

599
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:46,680
to expand into neighboring countries.

600
00:35:50,560 --> 00:35:52,080
Let me ask you honestly.

601
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:54,480
Do you really feel no guilt at all?

602
00:35:57,840 --> 00:35:58,920
Warat,

603
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:04,080
you're seriously misunderstanding me.

604
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:06,600
I really didn't do anything.

605
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:10,960
I was only
going to bring you to your room.

606
00:36:12,080 --> 00:36:13,480
You were unconscious,

607
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:15,920
and you couldn't get into your room.

608
00:36:17,680 --> 00:36:21,280
I was just going to let you rest and then…

609
00:36:21,360 --> 00:36:22,400
And then what?

610
00:36:26,160 --> 00:36:27,000
Forget it.

611
00:36:30,240 --> 00:36:31,360
It's my fault.

612
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:33,800
Let whatever there was between us…

613
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:36,040
Ameena, what exactly are you trying to do?

614
00:36:39,120 --> 00:36:41,240
I just came to talk business.

615
00:36:42,040 --> 00:36:42,960
Okay.

616
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:46,400
If you say there's nothing,

617
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:47,320
then fine.

618
00:36:51,560 --> 00:36:52,560
Go ahead.

619
00:37:07,440 --> 00:37:09,800
<i>Don't tell me your mom still doesn't know</i>

620
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:12,600
about your sister
being engaged to my grandson.

621
00:37:13,640 --> 00:37:16,400
No, she doesn't know yet.

622
00:37:16,480 --> 00:37:17,840
What is this?

623
00:37:17,920 --> 00:37:20,680
Something this big?
How could she not know?

624
00:37:21,320 --> 00:37:22,760
Didn't you say you were with your dad?

625
00:37:22,840 --> 00:37:25,240
We're adults. Don't act jealous.

626
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:26,720
It's unprofessional, you know?

627
00:37:27,440 --> 00:37:29,600
Det, I think you misunderstood.

628
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:33,040
Warat and I
really do have business to discuss.

629
00:37:33,120 --> 00:37:35,480
<i>What kind of business</i>
<i>requires lying down together to talk?</i>

630
00:37:35,560 --> 00:37:36,880
You're just a servant's child.

631
00:37:36,960 --> 00:37:39,240
Don't you dare get mouthy with me.

632
00:37:40,440 --> 00:37:41,800
Sin, don't!

633
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:45,800
I don't want to know anymore

634
00:37:45,880 --> 00:37:47,680
what's inside your aunt's room.
I don't want to know.

635
00:37:47,760 --> 00:37:49,360
Why? Why don't you want to know?

636
00:37:50,280 --> 00:37:51,960
Sin, turn around and look behind you.

637
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:55,200
NEXT EPISODE

638
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:56,200
What's wrong, Uncle?

639
00:37:56,280 --> 00:37:58,080
Uh…

640
00:37:58,160 --> 00:37:59,800
- Well…
- What did you do?

641
00:38:01,040 --> 00:38:02,440
It shattered in my hands.

642
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:04,360
Rat being

643
00:38:04,960 --> 00:38:09,280
Vanich's heir is already dangerous enough.

644
00:38:09,360 --> 00:38:13,240
What happened to you
may not have been a coincidence.

645
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:50,960
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
